sVbeer_ibu

sVbeer_description
p108
VAle Brewed with Rose Hips, Rose Petals, and Hibiscus. Let's face it, Beer is an art form that excites our senses and stirs our imagination. This truth gave Jolly Pumpkin an idea. We'd create a limited series of beer by throwing caution to the wind and following our creative muse no matter where it leads. This is how we discovered Baudelaire Beer. A romantic world, dimly lit by distant memory, yet alive and inspiring us to pursue beauty at any cost. In the world of Baudelaire, label and beer come together in character and art influencing the drinker to take upon the spirit of creativity and fun. Let the muse guide you. "A breath of air from the wings of madness." ~Baudelaire

VThe Great Pumpkin Ale :: An Imperial Pumpkin Ale. The Great Pumpkin was the silver medalist at the 2007 Great American Beer Festival in the Fruit and Vegetable category and was also the world\u2019s first Imperial pumpkin ale. Brewed with Pale, Munich, Cara-Hell, Cara-Vienne, Cara-Munich and Crisp 45° L Crystal malts. Roasted pumpkin seeds in the mash, and extra pumpkin added in the mash, kettle and fermenter. Spiced with cinnamon, nutmeg, cloves and allspice. 8% ABV

sVbeer_description
p1256
VThis is a beer made with real pumpkins. We hand-roasted over 500lbs of heirloom pumpkins from La Tercera Farms in Bodega Bay. The caramelized gourds were then added to our velvety American Barleywine and aged in brandy barrels for a year. Finally, we blended the barrel-aged beer with freshly brewed ale and added a delicate hint of pumpkin pie spices to round out this decadent autumn sipper.

sVbeer_description
p1684
VJolly Pumpkin Artisan Ales (Dexter, MI) and  Maui Brewing Co (Lahaina, Maui, HI) collaborated to create  Sobrehumano Palena \u2018ole or \u201csuperhuman\u201d. It is actually Maui\u2019s first collaboration in a can, brewed with passionfruit and cherries.  This is Jolly Pumpkin\u2019s edition of the collab.  Each brewery will add its own unique spin \u2013 as Maui will ferment normally (arriving in cans), and Jolly Pumpkin will make it  a barrel aged sour (in bottles). The beer was designed with two noble fruits from the two states Cherries & liliko\u2019i.

sVbeer_description
p2406
VUsing pumpkins grown just a half mile from the brewery, Gourdgeous also features traditional pumpkin pie spices and molasses. Rich with notes of dark chocolate, pumpkin pie, and sweet caramel, it's the perfect pour for when the days get shorter.\u000aThe pumpkins used in this brew were grown at Larry Jacinto Farms right down the street from the brewery. We were very excited when Larry told us that he had a great crop of pumpkins growing literally ½ mile from the brewery.  We had a fantastic team of volunteers who came to the brewery to help us seed and cut over 1,000 pounds of pumpkins and then we teamed up with Q-Works BBQ Catering who brought in big ovens so we could roast the pumpkins right here on site.

sVbeer_description
p3176
VFull Tilt Brewing's Patterson Pumpkin is a deceptively smooth Imperial Pumpkin Ale. This seasonal "feast" begins with a grain menu comprised of 2-Row Pale, Dark Munich, Red Wheat, and Carapils malts joined with Pumpkin in the mash. Sterling, Willamette, and Crystal hops are added to the boil to balance the malt sweetness. Finally, for the delectable pumpkin pie taste and aroma, cinnamon, nutmeg, ginger, allspice, and brown sugar are added; creating a rich, full-bodied, Fall drinking experience you'll want to revisit again and again.

p3367
VPunkuccino :: Coffee Pumpkin Ale. \u000aA pumpkin ale with the attitude of a world-weary barista, Punkuccino packs a short shot of Stumptown coffee toddy in your pint with just a shake of cinnamon and nutmeg.  Pale, brown, biscuit, C-77 crystal, chocolate and kiln-coffee malts provide the body, German Northern Brewer lends a touch of bitterness, and lactose sweetens just a touch. Three pumpkin additions, in the mash, kettle and fermenter. 5% ABV.

sVbeer_style
p3508
VPumpkin / Yam Beer
p3509
sVbeer_ibu
p3510
I21
sVbeer_description
p3511
VBrewed in the style of the farmhouse ales of Belgium's southern countryside, Hardywood Farmhouse Pumpkin utilizes a blend of rye, wheat and barley in the grain bill, earthy flavoring hops and a classic saison yeast. Ripe, flame roasted Virginia sugar pumpkins and brown sugar provide a hearty backbone to this 8.5% ABV beer. Freshly ground Ceylon cinnamon, whole Grenada nutmeg, whole Madagascar clove and whole allspice harmonize with pounds of freshly sliced organic ginger root.\u000aA beautiful hue of autumn russet, Hardywood Farmhouse Pumpkin displays a voluminous head, with a bouquet of aromatic fresh spice. Medium to full in body, this ale offers a balanced flavor of caramelized pumpkin and pie spices, with a lingering finish laced with a hint of fresh ginger.\u000aSugar pumpkins came from the Farm to Family Market on Mechanicsville Turnpike and from the Village Garden. Peruvian organic ginger came from Ellwood Thompsons Local Market in Carytown. Pumpkin Pie Spice came from C.F. Sauer, right around the corner from Hardywood. Whole Ceylon cinnamon, whole Grenada nutmeg, whole Madagascar cloves and whole allspice came from Penzys Spices in Carytown. All are local Richmond businesses.
p3512
sVbeer_name
p3513
VFarmhouse Pumpkin

sVbeer_description
p4226
VBig Black Jack is a rich, dark brown to black Imperial Porter with aromas of classic pumpkin pie spices\u000athat meld with dark cocoa notes. In the tradition of our forefathers in American Colonial Days, we\u2019ve\u000acrafted this Imperial Porter using pumpkins roasted by our patent pending technique, toasted pumpkin\u000aseeds, cocoa nibs, dark chocolate, and spiced it with cinnamon, clove, nutmeg, allspice and ginger (all\u000asourced locally). This malt forward ale begins with flavors of cinnamon and chocolate and are\u000ahighlighted by the toasty and chocolate flavors of the specialty malts. Ginger and allspice peek in from\u000abehind this medium bodied beer.

sVbeer_description
p6313
VWick for Brains is our classic and painstakingly produced Fall Pumpkin Ale.  Instead of simply using spice, we use real pumpkin which lends a sweetness and pumpkin flavor not found in many Pumpkin Ales. Wonderful pumpkin pie spice intertwined in an Amber Ale creates a pumpkin sensation which is elegantly crafted.  Notes of Cinnamon, Nutmeg, Clove, Ginger and Allspice blend perfectly in this seasonal Ale. There are many Pumpkin Ales out there crafted by some wonderful breweries \u2013 we feel that ours stands among them and in some cases \u2013 stands apart.

sVbeer_description
p6978
VImagine what happens when you take a nuanced cider filled with tannins and acid; smoke it over apple wood - the same wood that produced the apples - which gives it a light sweetness. Infuse that smoked cider with the earthiness of pumpkin. The apple juice steps back, allowing the smoke to be your first experience, followed by earthiness of the pumpkin and finishes with the acid of the cider.

sVbeer_style
p7262
VPumpkin / Yam Beer
p7263
sVbeer_ibu
p7264
I0
sVbeer_description
p7265
VMr. Yuck :: Sour Pumpkin Ale. Our sour pumpkin ale has an increasingly illustrious lineage, its inoculum having come from fermenter #2 at Tangletown, which has produced such beers as Krokus, Pandemonium, Pumpkin 8472 and well, Mr. Yuck a couple of other times.  As long as it's producing delicious and interesting beer we'll leave it just the way it is.  It all started with the Wyeast lambic blend, which somewhere along the way was lent out to the folks at Anacortes Brewing and came back with another couple of volunteers.  This time around we brewed Mr. Yuck at Elysian Fields, letting it ferment isothermally and then warm conditioning it for nearly three months before bringing it into the cold room for kegging and carbonation.  We think it's the best Yuck ever. Brewed with pale, Weyermann Munich, unmated wheat and flaked barley, incidentally bittered with Fuggles, with pumpkin in the mash, kettle and fermenter. 5.9% ABV
p7266
sVbeer_name
p7267
VMr. Yuck Sour Pumpkin Ale
p7268

VGourd of Thunder is a dark and gnarly Imperial Pumpkin Porter brewed with freshly picked local pumpkins that were ripened on the vine while continuously listening to heavy metal.  The malty pumpkin backbone fuses robustly with a milky sugar creaminess.  Bourbon vanilla beans lay down a rock-steady foundation that drives the cinnamon, ginger and clove spices through your skull.  This brew does not merely mimic the flavor of a mortal pumpkin pie.  Gourd of Thunder will cataclysmically blow your mind with its face-melting, high-voltage attitude.  Headbangers Unite!

sVbeer_style

VPumpkin / Yam Beer
p9989
sVbeer_ibu
p9990
I22
sVbeer_description
p9991
VIt had to happen sooner or later. We\u2019re referring to our Pumpkin Scratch Beer, of course! Realizing this monumental endeavor should not be taken lightly, our brewers explored the nether regions of the Pumpkin Ale spectrum to brew a serious beer suitable for the harvest season. Starting with a heavy fifty-pound load of neck pumpkins from Strites\u2019 Orchard, we roasted them to perfection right in our Snack Bar. To infuse the essence of fall, we added traditional pumpkin pie spices, cane sugar, honey, and vanilla. The use of French Saison yeast intensifies the spicy dryness of the ale and interplays nicely with the malt sweetness.

sVbeer_style
p10939
VPumpkin / Yam Beer
p10940
sVbeer_ibu
p10941
I0
sVbeer_description
p10942
VThis batch is fermented with an ale yeast as opposed to last year's lager batch.\u000a\u000aOur Brandy Barrel-Aged Imperial Pumpkin Ale pays homage to Lakefront\u2019s formative years and to our Wisconsin roots. It pours a copper-orange with a fine, off-white head. The aroma is caramel-forward, followed by cinnamon, vanilla, nutmeg, oak, and subtle brandy notes. The full, moderately bright mouthfeel starts  with cinnamon, nutmeg, and caramel malt, then yields Madagascar vanilla bean, oak, and brandy flavors. A lingering oak and malty sweetness are left on the palate; a reminder of how we\u2019ve honed our craft over the years.\u000a\u000a\u000aLike our Pumpkin Lager, this goes great with fall meals, but the intense flavors demand richer foods. Roasted or glazed foul will pair excellently: we suggest honey glazed turkey or roasted duck. Try sweet potato and butternut squash hash as a side, or a spiced butternut squash purée. Also a great a dessert beer: serve it with French vanilla ice cream topped with maple glazed walnuts or a simple bread pudding with dried cranberry and pecans.
p10943
sVbeer_name
p10944
VImperial Pumpkin

This fall seasonal tastes just like your mothers pumpkin pie, only in a glass and without whipped cream. Spicy cinnamon and nutmeg with the slightest hint of allspice will make you hooked and you\u2019ll find yourself reaching for a glass rather than a fork.

p13981

sVbeer_style
p14969
VPumpkin / Yam Beer
p14970
sVbeer_ibu
p14971
I22
sVbeer_description
p14972
VMade with locally grown white pie pumpkins, sugar pumpkins,  and Hubbard Squash.  Our brewers cut the pumpkins, sprinkle them with brown sugar (and love) and bake them in our brick oven.  The care taken in the brewing process is what helps make this orange-hued beauty a seasonal favorite.  It has a nice malt-backbone from the English base malt with the addition of aromatic and chocolate malts, we add nutmeg, brown sugar, cinnamon,and pie spices ...basically everything needed to make you feel warm and fuzzy inside.
p14973

p14974

sVbeer_description
p17721
VSmashing Pumpkin Ale is brewed to celebrate Halloween. It is a spiced ale - basically pumpkin pie in a glass. As well as British and German Malts, Murray's Pumpkin Ale also has over 80kg of dry roasted pumpkin added to the mash. The pumpkin adds a subtle sweetness and pumpkin aroma and flavour that is enhanced by the spice additions. Cinnamon, nutmeg and allspice are added late in the boil and blend well with the malt character of this unique beer.

p22275

sVbeer_description
p22276
VAs the story goes, the markings on the trees along the trail now known as Three Notch\u2019d Road, were made by axes chopping away at the bark. For this reason, the road was also called Three Chopt Road and today is labeled as such where the historic trail crosses through Richmond. Our Brewmaster will be chopping away, as well, into the 200 pounds of locally grown pumpkins for our Three Chopt Pumpkin Ale. \u000a\u000aThis fall harvest beer is a gathering of everything we know and love about the fall (except football). Laying the foundation is a nice hearty malt profile with a blend of caramel and crystal malts. The earthiness of the English hops go hand-in-hand with the festive spices of cinnamon, ginger and nutmeg and together make this beer the perfect autumn-time beverage.
p22277

p22278
VThree Chopt Pumpkin Ale

sVbeer_style
p22839
VPumpkin / Yam Beer
p22840
sVbeer_ibu
p22841
I45
sVbeer_description
p22842
VThe brewers added over 500 pounds of pumpkin into the mash as well as the kettle, where a mixture of fresh-milled spices joined Pilgrim and Columbus hops in the boil. The ale colors the glass like fossilized amber topped with a silky, persistent head of eggnog hue. Aromatic sprays of allspice, clove and baked pumpkin mingle with sharp, earthy bitter notes from the Columbus hops and stimulate the nostrils while the mouth salivates, awaiting the first sip. Once through the lips, Modern Day Pine-eer hugs the palate, embraced in turn by each set of taste buds. In keeping with the India-style way, the beer is drier than most of its peers, though the mouthfeel is remarkably firm and the finish crisp, but lingering.
p22843
sVbeer_name
p22844
VModern Pine-eer India Pumpkin Ale
p22845

sVbeer_style

VPumpkin / Yam Beer
p23169
sVbeer_ibu
p23170
I14
sVbeer_description
p23171
VStarting with over 100 pounds of pumpkin, this seasonal embodies pumpkin pie at its best. The design of this celebratory beer is to be sessionable, and not to wear out ones taste buds. Sit down and have a pint, or two, or three. There is a great balance of pumpkin, spice, and medium to high carbonation that ties this beer together. Available just before Halloween until it is gone (usually before Thanksgiving), this is one that you definitely do not want to miss.

VGolden Lager
p27203
sVbeer_ibu
p27204
I18
sVbeer_description
p27205
VWe start with 35 Jarrahdale pie pumpkins\u2014grown in Nunica, MI\u2014and roast them to perfection in our ovens. The resulting nutty, almost buttery pumpkin meat is then added to the mash of biscuity German malts on brew day. A judicious dose of pumpkin pie spice is then added during the kettle boil. The result is like Thanksgiving in a glass\u2014a delicious copper-colored lager balanced by just the right amount of pumpkin and spice flavors.

sVbeer_description
p30494
VThis Seasonal beer is brewed with 10 pounds of pumpkin per barrel of beer. It has an orange-brown color with the nose of pumpkin pie, brown sugar, nutmeg, cinnamon, and vanilla. As the Imperial Pumpkin Ale rolls across your tongue, you get the spice flavors finishing with a slightly malty sweetness and a alcohol warmth on your palate with a lingering urge to take another sip. Pope's Pumpkin comes in with a 9.0% ABV and a light hop level of 13 IBUs.

p31522
Vour first collaboration beer with a fellow Scottish Brewery, Cromarty Brewing.\u000a \u000aCromarty have been making awesome beers over the past few months and through the weird and wonderful world of Twitter and some crazy banter we hatched the idea to brew a beer together.\u000a \u000aEmails and call were exchanged, different beers were considered but it was decided we would take a crack at brewing a pumpkin beer! What had we let ourselves in for\u2026.\u000a \u000aThe beer itself uses a fairly complex malt bill, addition of pepper, some of our favourite hops and a barrow load of pumpkins. p37794

During the fermentation we add exotic spices and watch the magic happen. Pumpkin Spice Ale delivers a unique phenomenon when the taste of a beer is actually affected by the aroma as you drink it. Your taste-buds taste a smooth malt and slightly bitter while your\u000anose takes in the spice.

sVbeer_description
p38833
VThis specialty porter was brewed using over 80 pounds of fresh pie pumpkins. We also added a subtle blend of 6 different spices, and just a hint of roasted cocoa beans. The initial aroma is decidedly pumpkin. The beer hits the palate with notes of mildly sweet pumpkin pie, followed by subtle roasted malts and a mild but distinct chocolate finish.

sVbeer_description
p40007
V// Full bodied, Complex, Spice //\u000a\u000aFull-bodied, Complex, Spiced \u201cPumpkin pie in a glass.\u201d // Old Ale brewed with cinnamon, nutmeg, ginger, and allspice and locally grown pumpkin. As the days get shorter, the temperature drops, and the snow begins to accumulate, nothing warms the Fairbanks soul better than a slice of creamy pumpkin pie, topped with a dollop of whip cream. \u000a\u000aEspecially if this delicious treat comes in beer form. HooDoo Pumpkin Ale is made with over one hundred pounds of locally grown gourds from Rosie Creek Farm, and subtly spiced during the boil with cinnamon, nutmeg, ginger, allspice, and cloves. \u000a\u000aThe rich aromas from the baked pumpkin and light spice additions complement the deep malty base of this deep orange colored beer. Upon first sip, an up-front spice is immediately supported by a creamy, complex sweetness. The spices give way to rich maltiness before the beer finishes cleanly, but full-bodied. 
p40008

p40009
VPumpkin Ale (1st Anniversary Ale)

VOur Autumn seasonal. We used English Marris Otter with a touch of rye and caramel malt to create the malt base that reminds of pie crust, then added in Willamette and Kent Golding hops. To add the spice component, we used ground Saigon Cassia cinnamon, organic ground Peruvian Ginger, ground Grenada nutmeg, ground Jamaican allspice berries, organic Madagascar vanilla beans and pureed pumpkin. The result is a balanced and drinkable spiced ale. Have some before winter comes, and don\u2019t anger the Scarecrow!

sVbeer_description
p40762
VLike pumpkin pie in your glass. English pale and roasted malts create the sweet crust body. A fall spice blend added at the end of the brew to provide the sweet pumpkin spiced flavor. Lastly the finished batch was aged on real vanilla beans to emulate a dollop of whipped cream. The Baraboo pumpkin ale is pushed on nitrogen which results in a light velvety brew.

sVbeer_description
p55842
VIn 1944, President Roosevelt ordered that all troops stationed overseas were to get a real turkey dinner in time for Thanksgiving. A little taste of home for those fighting all over Europe and the Pacific. The boys over there called it \u201cThe Big Dinner\u201d; this beer brewed with real Pumpkin, Coriander, Nutmeg, Cinnamon, Ginger, and Vanilla, is our tribute.

I257776
sVbeer_style
p56584
VPumpkin / Yam Beer
p56585
sVbeer_ibu
p56586
I51
sVbeer_description
p56587
VThis is based on our traditional brown porter and it usually comes out just before halloween (which has recently become late for pumpkin beers - WTF?! - since when are pumpkins available in august?!!).  We wait for the fresh sugar pie pumpkins to come in, clean them by hand, dredge the pumpkin meat in spices, roast it low and slow, dump it into the brew kettle, and then throw a portion of the pumpkin right into the fermentor.  Brewed with nearly a pound and a half of fresh roasted sugar pie pumpkin in every gallon of beer.  This recipe was in development for for over 10 years, brewed in this form for the last 4, and in our opinion, is the absolute best pumpkin beer available (and I've tried them all!) -- not squashy, not overly spicy, this is a very full flavored beer that ages surprisingly well for it's low ABV.  Available on draft in the fall, with a portion set aside for bottle conditioning.\u000a\u000aSPECS:\u000aGrainbill:  Maris Otter, Roasted Barley, Cara Pils, Crystal 80, Chocolate, Special B \u000aHops: Northern Brewer, Cascades, Willamettes\u000aAdjuntcs: Pumpkin, Oak, Ginger, Cinnamon, Allspice, Clove\u000a\u000aABV: 5.2%\u000aIBU: 51\u000aSRM: 27
p56588
sVbeer_name
p56589
VSleepy Hollow Spiced Pumpkin Porter

sVbeer_description
p76535
VCerveza de aspecto ambarino intenso y con reflejos dorados, se presenta un poco turbia y con carbonico, aunque no abundante, presenta una burbuja fina pero lenta. La espuma, de color blanco perla, es de fácil creación. Esta cerveza está elaborada con maltas alemanas y belgas y lúpulos Hallertau. 6,2% alc. Esta cerveza acompaña perfectamente postres, gracias a su sabor especiado, como buñuelos de calabaza, tarta de manzana o tarta tatín.

sVbeer_description
p80870
VMalt balance is the key to our seasonal Cervecería Dos Aves Pumpkin Ale, providing a base for spices associated with the United States holiday season. At only 5.5% you can enjoy several of these beers with your American friends at their thanksgiving dinner and still have room for pie.**********La clave para nuestro ale de calabaza de la estación es el  balance en la malta, ofreciendo una base para las especias asociadas con la temporada festiva estadounidense. Las especias incluyen nuestra propia mezcla especial de pimienta dioica o inglesa (allspice), nuez moscada, canela y jengibre que evocan las festividades estadounidenses de Noche de Brujas (Halloween) y el Día de Acción de Gracias (Thanksgiving).  A solo 5.5% podrás disfrutar varias de estas cervezas con tus amigos estadounidenses en su cena de  Acción de Gracias y todavía tendrás lugar para la tarta de calabaza.

sVbeer_description
p112755
VBrewed in the style of the farmhouse ales of Belgium's southern countryside. Hardywood Farmhouse Pumpkin utilizes a blend of rye, wheat and Barley in the grain bill. Earthy flavoring hops and a classic saison yeast, ripe, flame roasted Virginia sugar pumpkins and brown sugar provide a hearty backbone to this 8.5% ABV beer. Freshly ground Ceylon cinnamon.  Whole Grenada nutmeg, whole Madagascar clove and whole allspice harmonize with pounds of freshly sliced organic ginger root.

sVbeer_description
p112993
VWe conducted a highly scientific study over the last few years and found that 95.3%* of "pumpkin" beers don't actually contain any real pumpkin. What gives? So, in response, we slaughtered over 200lbs of real pumpkin and brewed up this berleywine. Then we aged it in bourbon barrels with even more pumpkin, cinnamon, and Madagascar vanilla beans. So drink with caution because there's real pumpkin in this bottle (unlike the sea of wannabes out there).\u000a\u000a\u000a\u000a\u000a\u000a\u000a\u000a\u000a*Trust us on this one, we're great with statistics. Real pumpkins were harmed in the making of this beer.

If you like spiced and fruited beers then this will appeal to you.  Brewed with mild English hops and American yeast.  We used 36 pounds of pumpkin meat in our one barrel recipe. sVbeer
p122908
(dp122909

p122910

sVbeer_description
p122911
VPumpkinator is a big, black, full of spice, full of flavor beer. Originally released in 2009 as Divine Reserve No. 9, it is an imperial pumpkin stout and our answer to how a pumpkin beer ought to taste. This year\u2019s version comes in at 10% ABV. It is brewed with a combination of pale two row, caramel and black malts, Cascade and Liberty hops for a background hop flavor, pumpkin for a rich mouthfeel, molasses and brown sugar, and spiced and dry-spiced to make it feel like you just walked into your mom\u2019s kitchen while she was cooking 37 pumpkin pies. It is the most expensive beer we have brewed. \u000a\u000aA single batch of Pumpkinator will be released around every October 15. It is available in 22 oz. bottles and on draft.\u000a\u000aThis beer is best enjoyed at 50°F or warmer to bring out the spices and round body. Personally we have found it to be the perfect end to a Thanksgiving meal from a flavor standpoint. Some have said it makes relatives more enjoyable too.
p122912

sVbeer_description
p123007
VBishop's Barrel No. 6 is Pumpkinator aged in Appleton Estate 21-30 Year Rum Barrels. It smells like a pumpkin pie that somebody snuck some rum into. The taste begins with sweet malt, chocolate and spices followed by a warming rum finish. The pumpkin creates a pleasant body which holds up to the onslaught of flavors. It is oddly balanced with the hops creating a crisp finish - leaving the mouth wanting more. As it warms, all of the wonderful flavors become rounder and fuller.

sVbeer
p124383
(dp124384
Vauth_rating
p124385
I0
sVbeer_description
p124386
VPumpkin Ales are a bit of a tradition at Illawarra Brewing Co. Every year different beer styles have been used and ways of preparing the pumpkins. This year we kept Ashur\u2019s mums spice mix (we are talking allspice, cinnamon, cardamom, ginger, coriander seeds) and got our hands on some 20 year old American Bourbon Whiskey oak barrels, that have been used for rum in QLD since arriving in Australia. We doubled the pumpkin from last year(40kg), changed the malt and made it a bigger and better beer. The Rum Barrel ageing went nuts on this beer too, with a gorgeous nose reminiscent of a Jamaican spiced rum with notes of vanilla, coconut, smoke (the insides of the barrels are charred), sweet spice and cinnamon. 
p124387

sVbeer
p124478
(dp124479

p124480

sVbeer_description
p124481
VThis beer combines the rich, roasty flavors of a porter with those found in a traditional pumpkin pie. The complex aroma practically jumps from the glass. An intriguing mix of chocolate and spice\u2026 The flavor is robust with notes of dark chocolate, pumpkin pie and a caramel sweetness accentuated by a generous addition of molasses to the boil. The interplay of the cinnamon, ginger, nutmeg and allspice gives this beer a very pleasant finish. The pumpkins used in this brew were grown at Larry Jacinto farms right down the street from the brewery. Once the pumpkins were seeded and quartered, we teamed uup with the Gourmet Pizza shop in downtown Redlands to utilize their giant pizza oven to help roast all that pumpkin.
p124482

sVbeer_description
p128745
V2013 release. Hardywood Rum Pumpkin combines the nostalgic flavors and aromas of autumn with a soul warming, blackstrap molasses laced finish that can only be achieved through months of maturation in Caribbean dark rum barrels. Pleasantly mellow up front with a crescendo of pumpkin pie spice giving way to subtly sweet, lingering brown sugar and spiced rum notes, this beer might just bring new meaning to Thanksgiving.

sVbeer_description
p129780
VIt\u2019s a big stout brewed in the colonial fashion with large amounts of pumpkins and spruce tips added to the kettle for flavor and bittering qualities. The pumpkins complement the malt flavors and are used to add sugars to the mash. Whatever you do, do not think this is going to taste like pumpkin pie. For a SLOW experience, pair with BBQ venison loin, extra sharp cheddar cheese, vegetarian chili, fresh warm soft pretzel dipped in a honey mustard or grass fed beef stew.
